docs.abstract: It is the shopping phenomenon of our times, and now it’s an Amazon store.
docs.snippet: It is the shopping phenomenon of our times, and now it’s an Amazon store.
docs.lead_paragraph: In mid-November, as election post-mortems focused on inflation worries and the holiday shopping season began to pick up steam, Amazon introduced a new storefront.

docs.abstract: Within the boundaries of the crime-solving genius genre, “Cross” represents the dark yin and “The Lincoln Lawyer” the bright yang.
docs.snippet: Within the boundaries of the crime-solving genius genre, “Cross” represents the dark yin and “The Lincoln Lawyer” the bright yang.
docs.lead_paragraph: On the page, Alex Cross, the embittered psychologist created by James Patterson, leads his fellow fictional crime solver Mickey Haller, the flamboyant lawyer created by Michael Connelly, 32 novels to seven. On the small screen, the tables turn: The Haller series “The Lincoln Lawyer” debuted its third season last month on Netflix while the first season of “Cross,” announced nearly five years ago, finally arrives Thursday on Amazon Prime Video.

headline.main: ‘Cross’ and ‘The Lincoln Lawyer’ Offer Different Spins on the Same Formula
headline.print_headline: Darkness on the East Coast, Sunshine on the West

docs.abstract: Its shows have moved to Amazon Prime, where they will remain free.
docs.snippet: Its shows have moved to Amazon Prime, where they will remain free.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon is folding Freevee, its ad-supported streaming service, into Prime Video, where its shows will remain free to viewers who don’t subscribe to Prime.

headline.main: Amazon Is Phasing Out Its Freevee Streaming Service

docs.abstract: Mr. Bezos, who also owns The Washington Post, recently quashed the newspaper’s endorsement of Vice President Kamala Harris.
docs.snippet: Mr. Bezos, who also owns The Washington Post, recently quashed the newspaper’s endorsement of Vice President Kamala Harris.
docs.lead_paragraph: Jeff Bezos, the founder of Amazon and the owner of The Washington Post, on Wednesday congratulated President-elect Donald J. Trump on his victory, a sign of a potential thawing between Mr. Trump and the billionaire tech mogul.

headline.main: Jeff Bezos Congratulates Trump on Victory
